===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|la|catachrēsis}}, itself a borrowing from {{der|en|grc|κατάχρησις||misuse (of a word)}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{enPR|kătəkrēʹsĭs}}, {{IPA|/kætəˈkɹiːsɪs/|lang=en}},<ref name="OED"/>

===Noun===
{{en-noun|catachreses}}

# A [[misuse]] of a [[word]]; an [[application]] of a [[term]] to something which it does not properly [[denote]].<ref name="OED"/>
## {{lb|en|often, especially}} Such a misuse involving some similarity of sound between the misused word and the appropriate word.
# {{lb|en|rhetoric}} A [[misapplication]] or [[overextension]] of [[figurative]] or [[analogical]] [[description]]; a [[wrong]]ly-applied [[metaphor]] or [[trope]].<ref name="OED"/>

